	<ns6985:section xmlns:ns6985="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns6986:title xmlns:ns6986="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Window Managers</ns6986:title>
		<ns6987:para xmlns:ns6987="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		The window manager provides the desktop environmnet which includes features such as minimizing, shortcuts, panels and themes. Various options are available which each having benefits and negative aspects.		
		</ns6987:para>
		<ns6988:section xmlns:ns6988="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6989:title xmlns:ns6989="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">KDE</ns6989:title>
			<ns6990:para xmlns:ns6990="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			Mostly written in C++ provides a userfriendly enviornment and development libraries (QT). Provides a Windows look and feel. On the negative side it utilises a fair amount of memory. 
			</ns6990:para>
		</ns6988:section>	
		<ns6991:section xmlns:ns6991="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6992:title xmlns:ns6992="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Gnome</ns6992:title>
			<ns6993:para xmlns:ns6993="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			Gnome is written in C and in regards to userfriendlyness on par with KDE. With the inclusion of Nautilus a lot of eye candy has been added. The GTK libraries provides the backbone Gnome. Similar to KDE it consumes a fair amount of memory as well. 
			</ns6993:para>
		</ns6991:section>	
		<ns6994:section xmlns:ns6994="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6995:title xmlns:ns6995="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">WindowMaker - Gnustep</ns6995:title>
			<ns6996:para xmlns:ns6996="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			Very lightweight, yet amanzingly configurable. Provides extensive customisation options and can be used to lock / secure the desktop very easily.. 
			</ns6996:para>
		</ns6994:section>	
